Abby and Skye wish all of you a very happy and healthy Fourth of July 🇺🇸❤️
.
🌟Abby is very scared of fireworks and thunderstorms
.
I use prescription Sileo to help her anxiety along with a @thundershirtcompany
.
Please be sure to keep your animal in a safe environment and if you can stay home. There is no greater comfort like having you there
.
If your dog has aversion to loud noises look into getting a @thundershirtcompany and/or natural or prescription medication. We went through many trial and errors before finding Sileo. Sileo is the only FDA approved medication for canine noise aversion and must be acquired through your veterinarian
.
Make sure your dog has access to plenty of water
.
Make sure your dog is current with identification tags and a microchip. More dogs come into shelters today than any other day of the year
.
Be prepared. Know when the fireworks are going to start and turn up some classical music, the air-conditioning, a fan and anything else that will help block the noise
.
Do not panic. If your dog becomes alarmed maintain a cool and calm demeanor because your dog will feel your energy
.
Be sure your dog cannot escape. You’d be amazed how crafty these canines can get when they are anxious and scared
.
Tire your dog out during the day. There’s no better dog to get through anxiety than a tired dog. Exercise and mental stimulation will help you later this evening
.
Thank you for making Fourth of July safe for all of us 💙🇺🇸❤️

This is what the fourth of July looks like for dogs with reactivity to fireworks. We dose Abby early and watch over she and Skye Bear (who gratefully does not have any reactivity)🥹

Abby 
October 6, 2009 - August 9th, 2023
.
Yesterday afternoon we let Abby go - peacefully, surrounded by love, and in her favorite place in the backyard. Her sister Skye lie next to me as she gently left us.
.
My heart is shattered and in such profound pain, but I would do it all again. She gave her sweet love so freely, gifting our family with such profound joy. She spread that warmth to everyone she met. 
.
My last gift to her was a promise I swore I would always keep.  She left us with dignity and grace. And as the medicine took her final breath we told her how very much she was loved, and thanked her for being our sweet Abby.
.
Thank you to everyone in this amazing community who loves Abby. I will continue to celebrate her as I somehow grow accustomed to this new normal.

I miss her so much 🥹
.
I am humbled by your outpouring of love.  Your messages, posts, and comments have been so comforting. While the pain is so acute, knowing she is not suffering brings me immense peace.
.
